+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772754672056,"sessionID":"ses_33f96b1a8ffe2XNJFbSkALkDeg","part":{"id":"prt_cc069983e001vC61KePF6tSHCZ","sessionID":"ses_33f96b1a8ffe2XNJFbSkALkDeg","messageID":"msg_cc0697fd3002DeQ6Ilz6S03g4B","type":"tool","callID":"55d21d858","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: '**'\n---\n# Ralph Plan for In-Memory Task Queue System\n\n## Original request\nBuild a fully-featured in-memory task queue system that evolves through 12 phases, each adding capabilities (basic FIFO, named queues, priority, delayed tasks, retry with backoff, dead letter queue, task dependencies, concurrency control, progress/cancellation, recurring tasks, middleware, graceful shutdown). Export API from `src/index.ts`, implementation under `src/`. No external runtime dependencies.\n\n## Clarifications\n(Assuming no further clarification needed.)\n\n## Goal\n- A TypeScript library that passes compilation (`npm run build`) and lint (`npm run lint`).\n- All phases implemented correctly according to `phases/*.md` specs.\n- Comprehensive unit tests covering each phase's functionality.\n\n## Approach\n1. **Project scaffolding**: create `src/` files: `Task.ts`, `Queue.ts`, `TaskQueueManager.ts`, `index.ts`.\n2. Implement Phase 1: basic FIFO queue with Task class containing id (uuid), payload, status, timestamps. Provide API: `addTask(payload)`, `getNextTask()`, `getQueueLength()`. Export via `index.ts`.\n3. Write tests for Phase 1 using Vitest.\n4. Incrementally add features for each subsequent phase, updating interfaces while keeping backward compatibility.\n5. After each phase, run `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, and tests.\n6. Update README if needed.\n\n## Key files\n- `src/Task.ts` – task definition.\n- `src/Queue.ts` – queue implementation (named queues map, priority handling, etc.)\n- `src/TaskQueueManager.ts` – high-level API managing multiple queues.\n- `src/index.ts` – export public API.\n- `tests/` – test suites for each phase.\n\n## Risks\n- Managing many features may cause type conflicts; keep interfaces extensible.\n- Ensuring backward compatibility when adding parameters.\n- Implementing reliable priority and delay handling without external libs.\n- Concurrency may require async handling; ensure proper synchronization.\n- Recurring tasks need a scheduler loop.\n- Graceful shutdown must stop accepting new tasks and finish in‑flight tasks.\n\n## Mitigations\n- Use simple data structures (arrays, Maps).\n- Write unit tests after each phase to catch regressions.\n- Keep code modular and well‑typed.\n- For async features, use Promises and setTimeout for delays.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Create initial file structure and implement Phase 1.\n","overwrite":true},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772754672047,"end":1772754672055}}}}
